news.title: Ahmedabad civic body cancels permit, licences of HR Exeter-2 project
news.para: AMC officials said they visited the site after the accident and found that no safety measures had been put in place by the company.

news.title: Share of real estate in recoveries under IBC rises to 18.8%: Report
news.para: With a view to further streamline the corporate insolvency resolution (CIR) process, the Ministry of Corporate Affairs has invited comments on changes being considered to the Insolvency & Bankruptcy Code, 2016.

news.title: Shriram Housing Finance and Punjab & Sind Bank sign co-lending agreement
news.para: Shriram Housing Finance and Punjab and Sind Bank will jointly service the self-employed customers as per the co-lending model (CLM) of the Reserve Bank of India (RBI).

news.title: Cement volumes to expand by 9-10% in FY24: ICRA
news.para: The cement prices in FY2024 are expected to sustain at previous-year levels. Industry's operating margins to improve by 260-310 bps to 16.0-16.5% in FY24, according to Icra.

news.title: Chennai: 80% of identified buildings yet to be reassessed for property tax
news.para: The GCC had appointed Darashaw and Company Private Limited, which identified 3,10,139 buildings with deviations for reassessment and re-measurement. Of this, the corporation has remeasured only 60,000 buildings.

news.title: Can Fin Homes' net profit up 11.57% in Q2 FY24
news.para: Can Fin Homes' total income from operations stood at Rs 871.03 crore, a growth of 32.47 per cent from Rs 657.55 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Mukesh Ambani's luxury real estate bet gets HSBC financing boost
news.para: The London-based bank originally provided a £60 million ($73 million) loan facility to a subsidiary of Reliance Industries Ltd shortly after it acquired the Stoke Park estate in southeast England for £57 million in 2021, according to UK registry filings.

news.title: Gujarat's SGST department asks real estate developers to explain expenses
news.para: According to GST officials, around 20,000 notices have been issued to various taxpayers in across sectors, mainly for the 2017-18 financial year, some of whom are realtors.

news.title: Google leases office space in Blackstone's GIFT City tower
news.para: The company's Indian arm, Google India, has picked up office space from Nucleus Office Parks through a long-term lease of 10 years, including an initial term of five years and an option to extend it for five additional years.

news.title: Orient promoter CK Birla taps Adani for cement business sale
news.para: Industrialist CK Birla has approached Gautam Adani to sell his promoter stake in Orient Cement after rejecting offers from other buyers. Birla's stake in Orient Cement is 37.9%, with a market value of ₹3,878 crore.

news.title: Mahindra Lifespaces to jointly develop 37-acre plot in Mumbai's Bhandup
news.para: The property owner, industrialist K K Bangur, had been trying to sell the land for the past few years. However, there was no taker since the price quoted was a steep Rs 2,500 crore.

news.title: ADB approves $181 million loan to build infrastructure in Ahmedabad's peri-urban areas
news.para: ​The Ahmedabad Peri-urban Livability Improvement Project will construct 166 kilometer (km) of water distribution network, 126 km of climate-resilient stormwater drainage, 300 km of sewerage systems, and four sewage treatment plants, the Manila-headquartered multilateral development bank said.

news.title: Ajmera Realty to redevelop Balkrishan co-operative housing society in Mumbai
news.para: In September 2023, Anirdesh Developers, a subsidiary of the company, had signed a development agreement with the landowner for an SRA redevelopment project situated on LBS Marg in Bhandup, Mumbai.

news.title: Brigade Enterprises acquires 9.71 acres land in Hyderabad for Rs 660.28 crore
news.para: In September 2023, Brigade Tetrarch, a wholly owned subsidiary of Brigade Enterprises had entered into a sale deed for acquiring 5 acres 35.25 guntas of land parcel in Bengaluru for an overall consideration of Rs 123.50 crores from Bangalore Ceramics.

news.title: Sikkim CM announces housing schemes for those who lost homes in flash flood
news.para: Tamang said, "The Puranwas Awas Yojna (Rehabilitation Housing scheme) and the Janta Housing Colony scheme will be passed by the Cabinet on Tuesday and will be implemented thereafter."

news.title: Pune: Arbitration for Mhalunge Maan township to be submitted in November 2023
news.para: Around 510 plots and 5,800 beneficiaries have been finalised for the town planning (TP) scheme wherein beneficiaries get area equivalent to 50% of their land back in the township.

news.title: Belagavi: Kanabargi residential project to commence in two months
news.para: Buda hasn’t developed any new layout in the past 15 years, which has led to a tremendous surge in the land cost in the city. Ramtirth Nagar layout was the last residential project of Buda. Due to its underperformance, there has been a huge pressure on Buda to implement the Kanabargi project.

news.title: Calcutta HC orders BMC to demolish unauthorised Sector V building
news.para: Justice Abhijit Gangopadhyay passed the demolition order after the builder of the unauthorized construction didn’t comply with the court directive asking him to appear before the court.

news.title: How Raheja’s Leela Sky Villas stands out as a branded residency and redefines the idea of a luxury home
news.para: One such destination that has changed the face of this market in India is The Leela Sky Villas- Navin Minar in New Delhi. As the first managed residence branded by a 5-star hotel chain, The Leela Lace Holdings, in the city, it brings a slew of super luxurious amenities to those who want a lifestyle that reflects their success and showcases their accomplishments in life.

news.title: Country Garden's entire offshore debt to be in default if Oct 17 payment not made
news.para: Lack of payment - which is expected after Country Garden last week warned about its inability to meet offshore debt obligations - would make the firm the latest in scores of Chinese developers who have defaulted.
